1
00:01:18,500 --> 00:01:23,800
R O M E

2
00:01:32,334 --> 00:01:36,700
Announcer:
400 YEARS AFTER THE LAST KING
WAS DRIVEN FROM THE CITY,

3
00:01:36,767 --> 00:01:39,501
THE REPUBLIC OF ROME
RULES MANY NATIONS,

4
00:01:39,568 --> 00:01:41,733
BUT CANNOT RULE ITSELF.

5
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:45,301
THE CITY IS CONSTANTLY
ROILED BY CONFLICT

6
00:01:45,367 --> 00:01:48,767
BETWEEN THE COMMON PEOPLE
AND THE NOBILITY.

7
00:01:48,833 --> 00:01:52,334
POWER IS SHARED
AND ORDER MAINTAINED

8
00:01:52,401 --> 00:01:54,601
BY TWO SOLDIERS--
OLD FRIENDS--

9
00:01:54,668 --> 00:01:59,000
GNAEUS POMPEY MAGNUS
AND GAIUS JULIUS CAESAR.

10
00:01:59,067 --> 00:02:03,100
ONCE, POMPEY WAS ACKNOWLEDGED
BY ALL TO BE THE GREATER MAN,

11
00:02:03,167 --> 00:02:07,334
BUT FOR THE LAST EIGHT YEARS,
WHILE POMPEY HAS KEPT
THE PEACE IN ROME,

12
00:02:07,401 --> 00:02:10,501
CAESAR HAS WAGED A WAR
OF CONQUEST IN GAUL

13
00:02:10,568 --> 00:02:13,467
THAT HAS MADE HIM
EVER MORE RICH AND POPULAR.

14
00:02:13,534 --> 00:02:15,767
THE BALANCE
OF POWER IS SHIFTING,

15
00:02:15,833 --> 00:02:18,367
AND THE NOBILITY
HAVE GROWN FEARFUL.

16
00:02:18,434 --> 00:02:20,367
THOUGH OF NOBLE BLOOD
HIMSELF,

17
00:02:20,434 --> 00:02:23,134
CAESAR STANDS
WITH THE COMMON PEOPLE.

18
00:02:23,201 --> 00:02:27,401
A MAN LIKE THAT--
AN ARISTOCRAT WITH
SOLDIERS, MONEY

19
00:02:27,467 --> 00:02:31,267
AND THE LOVE OF THE PEOPLE--
MIGHT MAKE HIMSELF KING.

20
00:02:32,267 --> 00:02:34,267
( clamoring )

21
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:45,067
( yelling )

22
